docs.abstract: Chip Wade takes over Danny Meyer’s role in running Union Square Hospitality Group, a move that signals a growing conversation between two sides of the industry.
docs.snippet: Chip Wade takes over Danny Meyer’s role in running Union Square Hospitality Group, a move that signals a growing conversation between two sides of the industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: Anyone who witnessed the rise of fine dining in New York City during the 1980s and ’90s would hardly have bet that Danny Meyer — whose personal touch, food sensibility and laser focus on hospitality has influenced a generation of American restaurants — would pick a Red Lobster executive to replace him as the head of his restaurant group.

headline.main: From Red Lobster to Running Some of New York’s Marquee Restaurants
headline.print_headline: Fast Casual and Fine Dining in Conversation

docs.abstract: In his fifth, and possibly last, bid for president, Raila Odinga failed to enthuse a crucial bloc of voters in his own backyard that would have catapulted him to the top job.
docs.snippet: In his fifth, and possibly last, bid for president, Raila Odinga failed to enthuse a crucial bloc of voters in his own backyard that would have catapulted him to the top job.
docs.lead_paragraph: KISUMU, Kenya — For decades, Kenya’s veteran opposition politician Raila Odinga has been the chief political power broker in the western counties around Lake Victoria, relying on his fellow Luo ethnic voters to back him in five successive elections for president.

headline.main: How a Kenyan Power Broker Lost His Stronghold, Then the Presidency
headline.print_headline: Voting Bloc In Kenya, Once Loyal, Steps Back

docs.abstract: Investigators are looking into whether the man who tried to breach the F.B.I.’s field office in Cincinnati on Thursday had ties to extremist groups, including one that participated in the Jan. 6 attack.
docs.snippet: Investigators are looking into whether the man who tried to breach the F.B.I.’s field office in Cincinnati on Thursday had ties to extremist groups, including one that participated in the Jan. 6 attack.
docs.lead_paragraph: Investigators are looking into whether the man who tried to breach the F.B.I.’s field office in Cincinnati on Thursday had ties to extremist groups, including one that participated in the Jan. 6 attack on the Capitol, according to two law enforcement officials familiar with the matter.

headline.main: Man suspected of trying to breach the F.B.I.’s Cincinnati office may have Jan. 6 ties.

byline.original: By Alan Feuer and Adam Goldman

docs.abstract: The former president once asked his chief of staff why his military leadership couldn’t be more like the German generals who had reported to Adolf Hitler, according to an excerpt.
docs.snippet: The former president once asked his chief of staff why his military leadership couldn’t be more like the German generals who had reported to Adolf Hitler, according to an excerpt.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald J. Trump told his top White House aide that he wished he had generals like the ones who had reported to Adolf Hitler, saying they were “totally loyal” to the leader of the Nazi regime, according to a forthcoming book about the 45th president.

headline.main: Trump Asked Aide Why His Generals Couldn’t Be Like Hitler’s, Book Says
headline.print_headline: Trump Lament to Aide: Why Aren’t My Generals Like Hitler’s? Book Says

docs.abstract: More than a dozen N.B.A. arenas were used as voting sites for the 2020 election.
docs.snippet: More than a dozen N.B.A. arenas were used as voting sites for the 2020 election.
docs.lead_paragraph: The National Basketball Association said Tuesday that it would not schedule any games on Election Day, Nov. 8, in an effort to encourage fans, players and officials to vote.

headline.main: N.B.A. Won’t Play on Election Day, in Hopes of Encouraging Voting

docs.abstract: Officials said Ricky Shiffer, 42, was killed hours after trying to breach an F.B.I. office. Federal investigators had been looking into his possible involvement in the attack on the U.S. Capitol, two officials said.
docs.snippet: Officials said Ricky Shiffer, 42, was killed hours after trying to breach an F.B.I. office. Federal investigators had been looking into his possible involvement in the attack on the U.S. Capitol, two officials said.
docs.lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, Ohio — A man whom the police say they killed hours after he tried to breach the F.B.I.’s Cincinnati office had been on the radar of the federal authorities for months, two law enforcement officials said on Friday.

headline.main: Ohio Man Was on the F.B.I.’s Radar for Months
headline.print_headline: Man Who Tried to Enter F.B.I. Office Was on the Authorities’ Radar

docs.abstract: The record company apologized to “the Black community” for insensitivity in promoting an AI-backed artist that critics said was “appropriative” and included “slurs infused in lyrics.”
docs.snippet: The record company apologized to “the Black community” for insensitivity in promoting an AI-backed artist that critics said was “appropriative” and included “slurs infused in lyrics.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Capitol Music Group, the company that houses major record labels including Capitol and Blue Note, said on Tuesday that it was severing ties with its latest controversial artist: FN Meka, a virtual “robot rapper” powered partly by artificial intelligence, who boasts more than 10 million followers on TikTok.

headline.main: Capitol Drops ‘Virtual Rapper’ FN Meka After Backlash Over Stereotypes
headline.print_headline: Capitol Drops the ‘Robot Rapper’ FN Meka After Backlash

docs.abstract: The victory by Mr. Schmitt, the state attorney general, was a relief for Republicans who wanted to stop Mr. Greitens, the scandal-plagued former governor, from securing the nomination.
docs.snippet: The victory by Mr. Schmitt, the state attorney general, was a relief for Republicans who wanted to stop Mr. Greitens, the scandal-plagued former governor, from securing the nomination.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eric Schmitt, the Missouri attorney general, easily captured the Republican nomination for an open Senate seat on Tuesday, according to The Associated Press. His decisive victory derailed the political comeback of former Gov. Eric Greitens, whose campaign had been clouded by allegations of domestic abuse, infidelity and corruption.

headline.main: Eric Schmitt defeats Eric Greitens to win Missouri’s G.O.P. Senate primary.
headline.print_headline: Missouri Attorney General Defeats Former Governor to Win G.O.P. Senate Primary
